# BoardFlow Project Context

Monorepo: pnpm workspaces. Three packages:
- `apps/api` — Express + Prisma (port 4000)
- `apps/web` — Next.js 14 App Router (port 3000)
- `packages/shared` — Zod schemas + TypeScript types (imported by both apps)

## Multi-tenancy (CRITICAL)
- Every DB query MUST include `where: { tenantId }`.
- `tenantId` comes from `req.user.tenantId` (JWT payload). Never from the request body or params.
- Cross-tenant access must return 403, not 404 (404 leaks resource existence).

## Module structure
- `apps/api`: `modules/<domain>/controller.ts` → `service.ts` → Prisma only
- `apps/web`: `features/<domain>/` containing components, hooks, and api functions

## Validation
- All Zod schemas live in `packages/shared/schemas/`.
- Import from `@boardflow/shared`. Never redefine schemas locally.
- Always use `.trim().min(1)` for required strings — not just `.min(1)`.

## TypeScript
- No `any`. No implicit types. Use types inferred from Zod schemas via `z.infer<>`.
